; This solution tests that the Spanish SYNONYMS of the Predefined Player Words
; and other hardcoded input terms are all in place and working correctly.
; The definitions of these SYNONYMS can be found in the "gramática.i" module.
; ============================================================================
;                           PREDEFINED PLAYER WORDS
; ============================================================================
; These are the proper "Predefined Player Words", as described in Appendix E
; of The ALAN Manual...
; ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
; TEST: ALL WORDS
; ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Synonyms: 'TODO', 'TODOS', 'TODA', 'TODAS'.
toma todo
; ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
; TEST: AND WORDS
; ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Synonyms: 'Y', 'LUEGO'.
deja agua y refresco
toma agua luego toma refresco
; ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
; TEST: BUT WORDS
; ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Synonyms: 'EXCEPTO'.
deja todo excepto jugo
; ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
; TEST: THEM WORDS
; ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Synonyms: NONE! (TO BE ADDED)
; ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
; TEST: NOISE WORDS
; ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Synonyms: 'EL', 'LA', 'LOS', 'LAS' (definite articles).
; ============================================================================
;                         OTHER HARDCODED PLAYER WORDS
; ============================================================================
; Technically speaking, the SYNONYMS being tested here don't belong to the
; Predefined Player Words, but since they are predefined (hardcoded) words in
; the ALAN parser, and we had to provide translated SYNONYMS definitions for
; them, we're including them in this solution file too...
; ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
; NOTE: I'm not sure this is actually the case, for terms like 'IT', 'A', etc.
;       might be just the default fallback values defined on ENTITY for non
;       specified ARTICLES, PRONOUNS, etc. If the Spanish library defines
;       other defined values for ENTITY, these SYNONYMS might actually no
;       longer work. Need to check this!
